I'd give it 5 stars if it weren't for the smoke.  The place is cozy, great inexpensive drinks, pool table, juke box, the owner is great.  The problem is because it allows smoking, no one can go in without stinking like an ashtray.  Smokers go in filling the place with smoke, instead of drinking. Then the smokers stand right outside the door smoking so you can't escape.  If they didn't allow smoking, the place could be filled with professionals who love to drink but hate smelling like smoke. The bar would make a lot more money because the smokers would just drink more or go outside.  No one abandons their local bar because it's "non smoking", especially with how cheap drinks there are.  But people do abandon places that allow smoke because it gets known as a dirty dive bar. Can't go grab a drink without literally feeling a film on your skin and clothes. Wonderful atmosphere and service though.
